Github is the distributed version control system contrary to the Centralised version controls systems.
It provides the awesome environment for the developers to track and append the new changes in their earlier created projects.
It can be maintained in local system & server
commit changes saves the files & generates the hash id for each commit.
We can create many branches from the master and later merge the changes to the master.
Fork is to create a duplicate of the repository and then work in that repository.
Pull request is made by the user to implemeted changes in the new repository.

